race.description: The 56 Supported By Maccas Gippsland (Bm56) Handicap
race.comment: SOUTHERN CRESCENT (9) broke through for a smart win second at Stawell, coming from midfield off a solid tempo and racing away to win by 1.3 lengths. It was only a 0-56 there but the time was strong and this looks a winnable race if slightly tougher. Can do the double. BAMA SLAMA (7) is a lightly raced type who ran a solid race fresh at Pakenham in a Class 1. He should be improving now and draws for every chance. JESSUP (3) is going well without winning, beaten under a length at Cranbourne last time out. He'll roll forward and take catching. PURE SILK (13) was a barnstorming maiden winner at Werribee last time. Expect they settle a little closer from the middle drawn and he's thereabouts at the top of the straight. Can go on with it.
